<br>
You can go with the open channel random tells idea, but the thing to remember about it is you really need to have your raiding core set up before you open the channel.  If people join it, see that you've got no clerics, and the only tank is 46, or it's just you and two mages, they're gonna be out of there before you can blink.  Clerics also aren't much for spur of the moment tells for pickup raids, from my experience.  If you've got favors, call them in well in advance of when you want to go.  If people join the channel, see you've got a core of classes already in there, they're more likely to stay.  Most people rely on guilds for this because it's one way to almost guarantee that your raid goes down, although I have scheduled more than one raid where no one showed up before.<br>
<br>
Also, make sure you read up on Fear before you go in.  If it looks like you're unsure of yourself, people aren't as likely to commit, or you risk having someone else take over your raid and put you in the backseat, which can really screw up your chances of getting what you want.  If your raid is hijacked by a chanter, for example, and another guild zones in, they'll be more interested in protecting the wraith of a shissar than the BG.  When you do try Fear, do a West Wall Break.  Make sure people know that it's a West Wall Break before you go in.  Not only does that make it sound more like you know what you're doing, but it also completely trumps all 'the cult of personality' who might be trying to hijack your raid to do N wall and temples/CT/wraith first.  West Wall, then clear around the SW corner up to the Fright temple and the BG spawn is the easiest and fastest path to your epic.  Now, if there was just some way of guaranteeing he'd actually be up when you get there... <p><table width="350" border="0" bgcolor="#51260B"><tr bgcolor="#924614"><td width="125"><div align="center"><img src="http://www.muppets.com/profiles/graphics/StatlerWaldorf_s.jpg" width="125" height="108"></div></td><td width="177" bgcolor="#924614"><p align="center"><b><font size="3" color="#381A07">You are Statler or Waldorf!</font></b><font color="#381A07"><br><font size="2">You don't like dealing with most people, preferring to ridicule other people along with your equally misanthropic friend.</font></font></p></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#51260B"><td colspan="2"><div align="center"><font size="1"><b><a href="http://www.geraldfield.com/cgi-bin/unofficial/quizzes/sfesurvey.cgi?whatmuppetareyou" target="_blank"><font color="#C26A30">Take the <i>What Muppet Are You?</i> Quiz!</font></a></b></font></div></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC