<br>
If you have a decent number of tanks and enchanters, zone everyone in at once and fight right at the portal. Split tank and mez, or AE and stun, whatever suits your force best. When things stop coming, move to the west wall and start pulling.<br>
<br>
If that is too much, go in one or two groups at a time, running to the west wall. If anyone gets aggro on the way, they need to STOP immediately, and fight and die where they stand (unless they are a cleric). The most important thing is to get your clerics to the wall and camped. Everyone grouped with a cleric needs to sacrifice themselves to keep the cleric alive until camped at the wall. Secondary is killing as many mobs as you can in the process; that's that many less to deal with later. you also need to keep someone alive who can pull the corpses to the camp spot, a monk or rogue or both. Anyone who gets to the wall without aggro should camp immediately until everyone is in and your FD person says it is clear to come back.<br>
<br>
The trickiest thing about Fear breaks is the wierd aggro. Chain aggro is the rule there, and moving once you have aggro just spreads it faster. That is why you stand and die if you get aggro running to the wall camp. If you run with aggro, it just spreads faster - it is possible to aggro a large part of the entire zone running around. Your puller should be able to FD for the same reason, to break that chain aggro. <br>
<br>
Once you are all rezzed and re-buffed at the wall, clearing is easier by an order of magnitude, as long as your puller is reasonably competent. After a certain percentage of the wanderers are cleared, the rest become trivial. The golem himself can be killed with a single group of 60's, he not particularly hard, he just has a boatload of hp. With a full raid group, it's just a boringly extended fight (he takes a few minutes to kill instead of the few seconds the rest take). Slow him, tank him, take a nap. <p><script language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript">function stat_on(){self.status="Click for Magelo profile"}</script><script language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript">function stat_off(){self.status=""}</script><script language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript">function show_url(url_txt){newWindow = window.open("http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=" + url_txt)}</script><table><tr><td colspan = 2 align="center" style="filter:glow(color=#cc0000); cursor:hand" onClick=show_url("23437") onMouseover=stat_on() OnMouseOut=stat_off()  strength="1"><font size=2 color=#ffff00 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</font></td></tr>
