<br>
One thing you might want to try, is send up a few bards in first.  If there's one thing a bard can do well, it's make a train.  Also, they could charm those nearby mobs which are problematic to the raid, like scarelings, and take them out of the picture before you send in your main AE group.  After the AE group goes in, send in a second group of chanters and wizards as extras if you can afford them.  That way, if someone takes a DT from your break force, they'll have backup to pick up the slack.  <br>
<br>
Camp everyone already in Fear as soon as the break looks good, and have them log in again a little later.  This way, you're sure of an aggro wipe before the rest of the raid zones in.  If you want to be really careful, have all raiders camp in the first spot as soon as they zone in.  Provided no one buffs or heals until after everyone's relogged, all aggro should wipe.<br>
<br>
CT is the major problem with Fear raids, on the whole.  He is very easy to avoid or pull around, however.  Just avoid the E side of the zone when setting up camps, and you'll probably miss him.  He doesn't path behind the temple from the E side, as far as I've observed, so N wall behind the temple is probably safe.  SE corner is a problem spot, don't setup on that if you can help it.<br>
