<br>
Since that horrid event we have perfected the break and have done it dozens of times without incident. <br>
<br>
One 6 man group will do the break for you. They are your break group.<br>
<br>
Best group make up for this we have found..<br>
<br>
Chanter, Warrior, Cleric, Shammy, Wizard, Wizard/druid.<br>
<br>
You can sub any melee for the shammy if your chanter is an over achiever. The reason you use 2 evac'ers is to get your break group out even if one gets killed or teleported. <br>
<br>
The way to beat the break...chip away at it in small chunks. This is a must for lower level break groups!<br>
<br>
The Plan!!! <br>
 Zone in turn left and run down the hill to the wall . Make sure you are pre-buffed and all invis. You get to the safe spot with break group and just stand there in a little group till you get agro...no need to pull them the entrance area mobs will slowly path to you or agro on you. <br>
<br>
The goal is about a total of 15 kills near the entrance and the zone will be broke. Let your chanter do the CC and just be patient and do not panic. Kill as many as you have can given the number of mobs you will have in Mez root and snare. When mana gets low get out and come back for the next round. NOTE: To assist CC  &quot;All entrance mobs can be rooted and snared&quot;.<br>
 If you kill off 4 and cleric is getting a bit low on mana evac out to CT and run back and med up and go in again untill you have the 15 or so entrance mobs cleared. If your break group has to kill one or two and evac and do this 6 times in order to clear the 15 mobs or so at the entrance it will be faster than a corpse run!!! <br>
<br>
Before you zone in the rest of the guild for the raid make sure the break group is stable and have killed about 15 mobs in and around that safe spot that you run to just left and down the hill from entrance. Remember there is no need to pull these 15 or so mobs they will just agro on you  as you stand there at the wall. <br>
Number your groups G1, G2 and G3 exc. Zone them into Fear after the break is finished ONE GROUP at a time. The last thing you want is 15 lost peeps who will be running around not paying attention to drag dozens of mobs to the entrance because they turned the wrong way at zone in. One group at a time. When each group settles in to the groove of killing bring in the next groups...One person who does not know their left from their right can cause a wipe if they run back to the group after running even 20 feet the wrong direction and then turning around and training the groups at the wall. <br>
<br>
I know this sounds like a ton of work and effort but trust me if you spend an hour doing a correct fear break you will not have dead guild and a horrid Corpse run. I use this same plan even if i zone in with a lvl 65 chanter and he and I break the zone. Just slow and easy and let adds jump on you naturally...do not run or kite mobs or open that agro range up at all or you will have chain agro and a total mess.<br>
<br>
Good Luck with your break<br>
<br>
Krullis<br>
