<br>
Tips on composition (if not doing it AE)<br>
<br>
2 Tanks<br>
1 Chanter (60+ preferred)<br>
1 Monk<br>
1 Rogue with SoS<br>
*Healers - Honestly, if your tanks are in decent gear and are 55+ you do not need a single cleric unless you are going after Draco or CT.  You will though need at least one cleric for the sole purpose of rezing your monk from the random summon DT by Fright.  Substitute for CH able Shaman and Druids as needed.<br>
1 Shaman for Slows (Odd enough though I have had 3 60+ shammies that could not slow the BG on two seperate occasions)<br>
Then fill it up with dps<br>
<br>
The bare minimum I would go up there with is 12 for break in (if they work together well).  I would recommend 18-24 as that would make it all that much easier.  After you get above 24, you really start to see diminishing returns on break ins.  So avoid 24+.<br>
<br>
To break it:<br>
<br>
Monk in first and feigns.  Soon as the portal itself is clear you send in the SoS Rogue (Yes some stuff does see through the SoS in Fear but honestly its rare).  Rogue calls out to raid leader when the least amount of mobs in West Wall area are there and you all then rush into West camp.  (least amount we had on full pop in the way was 2).<br>
<br>
This is where I found it best:<br>
<br>
2 Main Tanks - Two Assists<br>
Half the raid with each one<br>
Of course a Enchanter is a must, but really if he is 60+ he will be fine and you can get by with just 1<br>
<br>
